<p>Robert Runcie, Archbishop of Canterbury, cooperated as Humphrey Carpenter prepared his biography, believing that the book wouldn&#8217;t be published until after his passing. Eventually <a href="https://archive.org/details/robertruncierelu0000carp_a8w6/page/384/mode/2up">he was forced to write</a>,</p>
<blockquote><p>
My dear Humphrey</p>
<p>I have done my best to die before this book is published. It now seems possible that I may not succeed. Since you know that I am not enthusiastic about it you are generous to give me space for a postscript.
</p></blockquote>
